06/05/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prosecutors filed corruption charges Thursday (May 5th) against 69 police officers and customs officials from three border checkpoints in the western part of the country. 
They are accused of having accepted bribes worth over 82,000 euros between October 2010 and January 2011 in return for ignoring cigarette smuggling between Serbia and Romania. 
The smuggled amounts are estimated at 3.3m euros. 
Thirty-eight of those charged are under arrest. 
Since February, a total of 182 people from the sector have been charged with corruption. 
(Hotnews.ro, Gandul, Evenimentul Zilei - 05/05/11)
